71-67 Jackson Street, at, adjoining and north of the N.W. corner of Front Street.
About 1900.
Wurts Brothers.

(1)
Front Street, west of, adjoining and at the N.W. corner of Jackson Street. St. Rose's Home shown across clearance (former sites of Nos. 368-384 inclusive) is at the corner direct and bears No. 71 Jackson Street. The building in the foreground with a wagon in front is No. 358.
March 23, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
A view of the cleared space and St. Rose's Home.
March 23, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)
A view of Nos. 354-356-358 solely.
March 23, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.
